The space
Casa de Paz (House of Peace) is like staying with family! If you want to experience San Francisco
like a local...instead of feeling like a tourist, this is the place for you.
Here you will wake up in your own peaceful room, with a view of San Francisco & the smell of fresh coffee brewing downstairs!

You may also enjoy the following amenities:
Use of kitchen
Internet/cable
Laundry Facilities
Beautiful Hiking right outside the back door! (Also, walking distance from the 49er stadium if you're a football fan!)
Less than 1 &1/2 blocks from public transportation (T-line light rail)
Minutes away from all main freeways, provides a quick commute

name: Mission District Private Yoga Room for two
description:
Take a moment for mindfulness. Give yourself the time to unwind and focus on the present moment in our clean backyard yoga Studio. Rent it for the Day and even stay the night. Comes equipt with a smart T.V. for you to follow a Yoga lesson or just kick back and watch a movie. It's your time. Located right in the heart of San Francisco's Mission District.

The space
Private Yoga room located in the backyard of our house.

Guest access
You can hang out in the front room and watch t.v., use the internet. You can also use the kitchen. You may store food, cook and use the microwave.

License number
City registration pending
neighborhood_overview: Great Neighborhood with many Restaurants nearby.
host_about: Hi. We are James and Mayumi. We will be your hosts. We have been married for a year now and love living in San Francisco. Mayumi is from Mexico and I am from here, San Francisco. We enjoy sharing our space with the Airbnb community and can give some great insight to the neighborhood. We enjoy Bike rides, Outdoor dining and Travel. We look forward to meeting you!
